2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses system design and maintenance challenges in large-scale social networks, which is a key area of software engineering. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses different partitioning algorithms and their trade-offs, which is a key area of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper discusses partitioning as a way to improve performance in social networks, which is a key area of databases. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the unique properties of social networks and how they affect partitioning, which is a key area of networking and internet architecture.
